structures.label: Articles against several of the clergy prepared for Archbishop Cranmer
Accounts for the imprisonment and execution of Cranmer, Latimer and Ridley
Biography of Thomas Cranmer, Archbishop of Canterbury

description: MS 128 contains a collection of sixteenth-century documents bound together due to their connections with Thomas Cranmer, Archbishop of Canterbury. The volume contains a collection of accusations against clergy opposed to Cranmer, accounts for the imprisonment and execution of Cranmer, Latimer and Ridley in Oxford (including a request for payment of money still owing) and a biography of Archbishop Cranmer.
